commitResults.messageTitle: Add save mechanism for current session
commitResults.messageBody:
- Add session domain model, JSON adapters, and recorder to capture command history and active filters
- Wire new session storage into LogicManager, StorageManager, and MainApp to save snapshots alongside prefs
- Document the session schema and extend unit tests for logic and storage integration

- store each shutdown snapshot in data/sessions/session-<timestamp>-<zone>.json, generated from the session’s savedAt instant plus the local time zone.
- autoload the latest snapshot on startup, restore its search filter, and seed the session recorder so history persists across runs.
- refactored storage APIs to operate on a session directory, updated JSON adapter to enumerate snapshots, and refreshed docs/tests to cover the new behavior.
